1 Section 1. NEW SECTION. 53.5 Absentee ballot marking pilot
2 program.
3 1. The state commissioner may adopt rules pursuant
4 to chapter 17A to implement a pilot program to establish
5 procedures to enable a voter with a disability that prevents
6 the voter from marking a ballot by hand to independently and
7 privately mark a ballot or use an electronic voting device that
8 produces a paper record using nonvisual access, low-vision
9 access, or other assistive technology in order for the voter to
10 complete an absentee ballot by mail pursuant to this chapter.
11 The procedures must include a method by which a voter with a
12 disability that prevents the voter from marking a ballot by
13 hand to request an absentee ballot by mail.
14 2. If the pilot program under this section is not
15 implemented statewide, the pilot program must include a
16 sufficient number of counties, as determined by the state
17 commissioner, to conclude whether the program is feasible
18 statewide.
19 3. The state commissioner shall file a report with the
20 general assembly by December 31 of each year regarding the
21 pilot program established under this section.
22 4. This section is repealed July 1, 2026.
23 EXPLANATION
24 The inclusion of this explanation does not constitute agreement with
