26 This bill allows the state commissioner of elections to
27 adopt rules to establish a pilot program to allow voters with
28 disabilities that prevent such voters from marking ballots by
29 hand to independently and privately mark absentee ballots,
30 including by the use of assistive technology. The bill
31 requires that the program include a method by which such voters
32 can request an absentee ballot by mail.
33 If the pilot program under the bill is not established
34 statewide, the bill requires that the program be established
35 in a sufficient number of counties to allow the state
